happign

The goal of happign is to facilitate the use of Application Programming Interface from the French National Institute of Geographic and Forestry Information.

Installation

You can install the released version of happign from CRAN with:

install.packages("happign")

And the development version from GitHub with:

# install.packages("devtools")
devtools::install_github("paul-carteron/happign")

Basic use

Please check package vignette “Getting_started” for basic use of happign or articles on the website

browseVignettes("happign")

Problems and Issues

  • Please report any issues or bugs you may encounter on the dedicated page on github.

System Requirements

happign requires R v >= 4.1.0.
